					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex. </support>
								<extent rend="visible">295 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>226</height>
										<width>156</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>154</height>
										<width>100</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>295 folios (+ 6 unfoliated flyleaves at the beginning and 4 unfoliated flyleaves at the end of the manuscript). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>30 quires of 10 leaves, except from the last quire which has 6 leaves extant.</p>
									<p>Quires are signed with Hebrew letters on the first and last pages, and marked with catchwords on the last page.</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="26 28" writtenLines="26 28">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Visible vertical (page by page) plummet ruling and horizontal (page by page) ink ruling. </p>
									<p>Graphic filler at the end of line. Last written line within ruling. </p>
									<p>Hair side and flesh side of folios distinguishable. </p>
									<p>Deuteronomy, Song of Songs, Lamentations, Psalms, Proverbs and Hafṭarot commence a new leaf.</p>
									<p>Initial word of each book written in larger letters.</p>
									<p>Beginning of a pericope in the Pentateuch marked by פרש', accompanied with a small pen and ink design.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Sefardi square script of the 15th century, punctuated and accentuated. <name type="person" role="scribe">Abraham Farissol [of Avignon]</name>, son of Mordekhai Farissol, inscribed with his name in colophon, folio 293v.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Yeḥiel Foah</name>, inscribed with his name on folio 293v: זה החומש עם ההפטרות ותלים משלי איוב וה&apos; מגילות של היקר כמר&apos; יחיאל פואה יצו&apos; אחרי חלוק האחי&apos; ... ה&apos; למען חסדיו יזכהו להגות בו הוא וזרעו וזרע זרעו עד סוף כל הדורות אכיר&apos;. </p>
							<p>Partially erased Hebrew inscription, folio 294v, with tan oath and the names of five witnesses, dated <date calendar="Hebrew">251</date> (<date calendar="Gregorian">1491</date>). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="patron">Shemu᾿el of Pula</name> (?), inscribed with his name on folio 1v, with a list of his sons (faded ink). </p>
							<p>Anonymous censorial note is given on folio 294v: Io fra luigi lo uidi del 1599.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Post-1600. Morocco binding, gold-tooled. </p>
								<p>Spine: &apos;Codex Biblicus Hebraice. Mus. Brit. Ex Dono Sol. da Costa. 4709.&apos;</p>
							</binding>
